Early on in my career, one of the hardest lessons I learned was when *I
neglected to check my camera settings* before snapping a shot.

It cost me *thousands of dollars* and time to figure out what went wrong.

The photo itself wasn't worth taking and in addition there were *all the
costs tied up in it.* That's why I take my entire creative process
*seriously* now.

It may sound like too much work for just one photo, but the old saying is
true: "you only get one shot to take."

I want to show a simple method I use that will help you be confident and
creative when you are out there and *I wanted to share it with you before
the link expires.*
